The road race world championship of 2012

The road race world championship of 2012

Of 2012
The FIM road race world championship
In the previous year: 2011 The next year: 2013

The road race world championship of 2012 becomes the 64th meeting of the FIM road race world championship.

Table of contents

Summary of the season

It was the held first year of the Moto3 class for the 125cc class in current season. In the MotoGP class of the highest peak, a season began as a defending champion Casey ストーナー and Honda [1]. Of the champion of the Moto2 class, the Stephane bra dollar LCR Honda MotoGP step-up [2], in the same way 125cc class champion Nicholas テロル performed step-up from team asper in Moto2 [3].

Change of the class

As for the engine of the MotoGP class, the displacement volume was raised to up to 1,000cc (61 cu in), and the greatest dimension of the cylinder was prescribed at 81mm (3.2 in) if the number of the cylinders was lower than four-cylinder [4]. The participation in a war with the machine equipped with the engine which was higher than 5 cylinders was prohibited by this change.

In addition, Moto3 class equipped with 4 stroke 250cc single-cylinder engines in place of 2 stroke 125cc will be held [5].

クレーミング rule team

クレーミング rule team (Claiming Rule Teams, CRT) in consideration of the participation by the low-budget independent team is introduced in a season in 2012. As for the CRT, 12 engines, more fuel (24 liters) and limits are relaxed per rider, but must sell it in the state including the transmission for 15,000 dollars or 20,000 dollars when a factory team attaches purchase of the engine or "クレーミング" [6]. We had a participation application in the CRT rule by 16 new teams in the first year [7].

New entry

The FIM announced new six teams which participated in the Moto2 class in June, 2011. - インターウェッテン paddock, forward racing, mark VDS, kieffer racing, speed master, BQR- bulldog sense (switch to アヴィンティア racing later) [8] - The entry was approved [9]. Two teams were added afterwards. - Pole bird motor sports[10], イオダ racing[11] - However, the インターウェッテン paddock, mark VDS, the kieffer racing were off the revision release that FIM announced in January, 2012 [12].

Grand prix

On September 14, 2011, all holding calendars consisting of 18 were announced than FIM [13]. In the modified schedule announced three months later, GP in Qatar became the moving up for one week [14].
